        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 1 at 2:16PM PDT by NWS Reno NV</headline>
        <description>At 216 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Cold Springs, or 10 miles southeast of Chilcoot, moving north at 15
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hallelujah Junction, Cold Springs, Cold Springs Valley, Us 395 At
Calif-Nevada Line Near Bordertown, and Us 395 At Sierra-Lassen Co
Line.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
